  "prompt": "What are some best hotel in Jaipur?",
  "response": "Jaipur has a fantastic range of hotels, from opulent palaces to charming boutique stays. To recommend the \"best\" for you, I need a little more information!  However, I can give you a list of some highly-rated and popular options, broken down by general categories, so you can find something that suits your needs:\n\n**Luxury/Palace Hotels (High-End, Expect to Pay a Premium):**\n\n*   **Rambagh Palace:**  (Taj Group)  Undoubtedly one of the most famous and luxurious hotels in the world.  A former palace, offering unparalleled service, stunning architecture, and lavish experiences.\n\n*   **The Oberoi Rajvilas:**  Another breathtakingly beautiful hotel, with luxurious tents, gardens, and impeccable service. Offers a very serene and romantic atmosphere.\n\n*   **Taj Jai Mahal Palace:** A gorgeous heritage hotel with lush gardens, beautiful architecture, and a regal ambiance.\n\n*   **ITC Rajputana, a Luxury Collection Hotel, Jaipur:** Contemporary luxury with a blend of traditional Rajasthani design. Known for excellent service and dining options.\n\n**Boutique/Heritage Hotels (Unique Charm and Character):**\n\n*   **Samode Haveli:**  A beautifully restored Haveli (traditional mansion) with stunning courtyards, intricate artwork, and a very authentic Rajasthani feel.\n\n*   **Alsisar Haveli:**  Another lovely Haveli with character, charm, and a great location in the city.  Known for its beautiful interiors and friendly staff.\n\n*   **Hotel Diggi Palace:** Famous for hosting the Jaipur Literature Festival, this palace offers a taste of history and culture.\n\n*   **Shahpura House:** A heritage hotel that offers a blend of traditional Rajasthani hospitality with modern amenities.\n\n**Mid-Range Hotels (Good Value and Comfort):**\n\n*   **Umaid Bhawan - A Heritage Style Boutique Hotel:**  Offers a good balance of comfort, style, and affordability. Often praised for its cleanliness and friendly staff.\n\n*   **Lalit Jaipur:** Good reliable options in mid range segment.\n\n*   **Four Points by Sheraton Jaipur, City Square:** A popular choice for business and leisure travelers alike.\n\n**Things to Consider When Choosing:**\n\n*   **Budget:** Prices vary wildly. Determine how much you're willing to spend per night.\n*   **Location:**  Do you want to be in the heart of the city (closer to sights, but potentially more crowded) or on the outskirts (more peaceful, but requiring transport)?\n*   **Travel Style:** Are you looking for ultimate luxury, a romantic getaway, a family-friendly option, or something more budget-conscious?\n*   **Amenities:**  Do you need a pool, spa, on-site restaurants, a business center, etc.?\n*   **Reviews:**  Check recent reviews on sites like TripAdvisor, Booking.com, and Google to get an idea of other guests' experiences.\n\n**To give you a more personalized recommendation, please tell me:**\n\n*   **What's your budget per night?** (e.g., Under $50, $50-$100, $100-$200, $200+)\n*   **What kind of experience are you looking for?** (Luxury, romantic, family-friendly, cultural, budget-friendly, etc.)\n*   **What's important to you in a hotel?** (Location, pool, service, amenities, etc.)\n*   **When are you traveling?** (Prices can fluctuate significantly depending on the season)\n\nOnce I have this information, I can provide a much more tailored and helpful recommendation.\n",
